<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>Welcome to AutoProfix Garage Management System! This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information. By using our services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>

<h3>Registration Information</h3>
<p>When you create an account with AutoProfix Garage Management System, we collect your name, email address, and other contact information.</p>

<h3>Vehicle and Maintenance Data</h3>
<p>We collect information related to vehicles, including brand, model, year, chassis number, mileage, and maintenance history. This data is used for garage management and record-keeping.</p>

<h3>Appointment Details</h3>
<p>If you schedule appointments through our system, we collect appointment details, including dates, times, and services requested.</p>

<h3>Invoicing and Payment Information</h3>
<p>When you use our invoicing and payment services, we collect payment information, such as billing addresses and payment card details. We use secure third-party payment processors to handle payments, and we do not store payment card information on our servers.</p>

<h3>Customer Data</h3>
<p>We may collect and store data related to our customers, including contact information and vehicle history, to provide better services.</p>

<h3>Inventory Management</h3>
<p>For inventory management, we collect data on stock levels and materials used.</p>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>

<h3>Providing Services</h3>
<p>We use the collected information to provide and maintain our garage management services, including vehicle registration, maintenance tracking, appointment scheduling, and more.</p>

<h3>Communication</h3>
<p>We may use your contact information to send important updates, notifications, and promotional offers. You can opt out of promotional communications at any time.</p>

<h3>Improving Our Services</h3>
<p>We analyze usage patterns and customer feedback to improve our services, including enhancing the user experience, adding new features, and fixing issues.</p>

<h2>Disclosure of Your Information</h2>

<p>We may share your information with third-party service providers, business partners, or government authorities as required by law.</p>

<h2>Security</h2>

<p>We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.</p>

<h2>Your Choices</h2>

<p>You can review, update, or delete your personal information by accessing your account settings. You may also request the removal of your account by contacting us.</p>

<h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version will be posted on our website, and we encourage you to review it regularly.</p>

<h2>Contact Us</h2>

<p>If you have any questions, concerns, or feedback regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [Contact Information].</p>
